CROATIA: Saudi Minister of Islamic Affairs, Dawah and Guidance Sheikh Abdullatif Al-Asheikh and his accompanying delegation visited the Islamic Cultural Center in Zagreb, Croatia, which was established in 1980 and opened in 1987.
	During the visit, the minister learned about the construction and foundation of the grand mosque at the center, one of the most important Islamic milestones in Croatia.
	The Saudi minister was also briefed on the centerâ€™s scientific, charitable, cultural and social activities.
	The minister toured the Islamic Scientific Secondary School affiliated with the Ministry of Education in Croatia, stressing the importance of education during a meeting with students.